<TITLE> CHT taskforce on refugees starts work </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khagrhachharhi, Oct 5 (bdnews24.com)A meeting of the Chittagong Hill Tracts taskforce on repatriation and rehabilitation of indigenous refugees and identification and rehabilitation of the internal refugees began on Monday at Khagrhachharhi circuit house. The taskforce chairman Jatindra Lal Tripura said invitation had been sent to all the 10 members of the committee. The task force, mandated by Chittagong Hill Tracts Peace Accord, was constituted on January 20, 1998 to address refugee problems. Kalparanjan Chakma, Dipankar Talukdar and Shamiran Dewan served as chairman of the taskforce at different tenures. Recently, Jatindra Lal Tripura was appointed chairman and a 10-member committee was reconstituted. The committee members are : Khagrhachharhi hill district council chairman Ruithi Karbari, Khagrhachharhi deputy commissioner Md Abdullah, Chittagong division assistant commissioner MAN Siddique, Bandarban deputy commissioner Md Abdul Mannan, Bandarban hill district council member Aung Pro Mrong, Rangamati additional deputy commissioner Md Khalilur Rahman, Khagrhachharhi army headquarters zonal representative major Lokman, Khagrhachharhi district Awami League leader SM Shafi and India-repatriated refugees welfare committee secretary Sontushito Chakma Bakul. bdnews
